ited States. Seen in that context, today's international directors are less analogous to the emigre talent of the past than to ordinary transnational employees of other major global corporations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMotion picture industryxFinance. 0aMotion picture producers and directors. 0aMotion pictures and globalization. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and direction. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aHollywood Cinema. 7aART / Film & Video.2bisacsh  aGlobalization, Cultural Industries, Hollywood, Transnational Cinema.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066293140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048524976zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048524976423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048524976.jpg  a978-3-11-060644-7  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066293-1  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK